item.title: Judge blocks Trump National Guard deployment to Portland, citing lack of justification
item.description: U.S. District Court Judge Karin Immergut on Sunday temporarily extended an order blocking the Trump administration from deploying National Guard troops to Portland, Oregon, saying the government failed to justify the move.vIn an order issued Sunday evening, Immergut "preliminarily enjoins Defendant Secretary of Defense Hegseth from implementing" memorandums that authorized the federalization and deployment of National Guard members from Oregon, Texas and California into Portland.
